#: {{ux|en|We had a wholesome, filling meal, '''free''' of meat.&emsp; I would like to live '''free''' from care in the mountains.}}
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|author={{w|Gilbert Burnet}}| title=The History of the Reformation of the Church of England| year=1679-1715| passage=princes declaring themselves '''free''' from the obligations of their treaties}}
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=1898|author={{w|Winston Churchill (novelist)|Winston Churchill}}| title={{w|The Celebrity}}| chapter=4| passage=One morning I had been driven to the precarious refuge afforded by the steps of the inn, after rejecting offers from the Celebrity to join him in a variety of amusements. But even here I was not '''free''' from interruption, for he was seated on a horse-block below me, playing with a fox terrier.}}
#: {{syn|en|without}}
