===Verb===
[[File:Peter Paul Rubens - Perseus Freeing Andromeda - WGA20306.jpg|thumb|A painting depicting mythical Greek hero Perseus '''freeing''' Andromeda, who was imprisoned by a sea monster]]
{{en-verb|d}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make free; set at [[liberty]]; [[release]]; rid of that which confines, limits, embarrasses, or oppresses.
#* {{circa|1610-11}} {{w|William Shakespeare}}, ''{{w|The Tempest}}'', Act I scene ii<sup>[http://www.opensourceshakespeare.org/views/plays/play_view.php?WorkID=tempest&Scope=entire&pleasewait=1&msg=pl]</sup>:
