#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=1986|author=David Barrat|title=Media Sociology|isbn=041505110X|page=112|passage=The '''word''', whether written or spoken, does not look like or sound like its meaning ‚Äî it does not resemble its signified. We only connect the two because we have learnt the code ‚Äî language. Without such knowledge, 'Maggie' would just be a meaningless pattern of shapes or sounds.}}
