==Afrikaans==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|af|nl|worden}}, from {{inh|af|dum|werden}}, from {{inh|af|odt|werthan}}, from {{inh|af|gem-pro|*wer√æanƒÖ}}.

===Verb===
{{af-verb}}

# to [[become]]; to [[get]] {{gloss|to change one‚Äôs state}}
#: {{ux|af|Ek het ryk '''geword'''.|t=I '''became''' rich.}}
#: {{ux|af|Ek '''word''' ryk.|t=I '''am becoming''' rich.}}
#: {{ux|af|Sy '''word''' beter.|t=She '''is getting''' better.}}
# {{non-gloss definition|Forms the present passive voice when followed by a past participle}}
#: {{ux|af|Die kat '''word''' gevoer.|t=The cat '''is being''' fed.}}

====Usage notes====
* The verb has an archaic preterite '''{{m|af|werd}}''': ''Die kat <u>werd</u> gevoer.'' (‚ÄúThe cat <u>was</u> fed.‚Äù) In contemporary Afrikaans the perfect is used instead: ''Die kat <u>is</u> gevoer.''

