====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To block the flow of water so that it can escape only through evaporation or seepage; to [[dam]].
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=2004|author=Calvin W. Rose|title=An Introduction to the Environmental Physics of Soil, Water and Watersheds|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=TxCQ-DaSIwUC ISBN 0521536790|page=201|passage=The rate of fall of the surface of water '''ponded''' over the soil within the ring gives a measure of the infiltration rate for the particular enclosed area.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make into a pond; to collect, as water, in a pond by damming.
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To form a pond; to [[pool]].

===Etymology 2===
{{clipping|en|ponder}}.

====Verb====
