==Latin==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|la|a}} {{qual|in some abbreviations}}

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|la|grc|Œë|t=alpha}}, likely through Etruscan.

===Pronunciation===
* {{la-IPA|eccl=yes}}
* {{audio|La-ecc-A.ogg|audio (ecclesiastical)|lang=la}}

===Letter===
{{la-letter|upper=A|lower=a}}

# {{lb|la|sometimes with ''[[littera]]''}} {{Latn-def|la|letter|1}}

====Usage notes====

* In compound words, long ''ƒÅ'' generally remains unchanged ({{m|la|lƒÅbor}}, {{m|la|dƒìlƒÅbor}}). In a non-initial syllable, short ''ƒÉ'' is changed by {{w|vowel reduction}} into short ''ƒ≠'' or short ''ƒï'' ({{m|la|tang≈ç}}, {{m|la|conting≈ç}}; {{m|la|capi≈ç}}, {{m|la|concipi≈ç}}, {{m|la|conceptum}}). It remains unchanged in cases in which the word was coined later on: {{m|la|am≈ç}}, {{m|la|adam≈ç}}; {{m|la|patiƒìns}}, {{m|la|impatiƒìns}}.

===Abbreviation===
{{head|la|abbreviation|head=A.}}

# {{lb|la|in dates}} ''[[ante]]'' (‚Äúbefore‚Äù)
#: '''''A.''' D.'' ‚Äî ''ante diem''
# {{lb|la|in dates}} ''[[anno]]'', ''[[annus]]'' (‚Äúyear‚Äù)
#: '''''A.''' D.'' ‚Äî ''anno Domini''
#: '''''A.''' U. C.'' ‚Äî ''anno urbis conditae''
#: '''''A.''' P. R. C.'' ‚Äî ''anno post Romam conditam''
# [[Aulus]] (a Roman given name)
#* Inscriptiones Orelli 1530: '''''A'''. '''A.''''' ‚Äî ''Auli duo''
# [[aquae]] (‚Äúwaters‚Äù)
#* Inscriptiones Orelli 1643 sequens; 2620; 3011: '''''A.A.''''' ‚Äî ''Aquae Aponi'' (‚Äú[[w:Abano Terme|Abano Terme]]‚Äù)
# ''[[auro]]'', ''[[argento]]'', or ''[[aeri]]'' (the three directors of the mint)
#* Inscriptiones Orelli 569; 2242; 2379; 3134 alia: ''III. VIRI '''A.''' '''A.''' '''A.''' F. F.'' ‚Äî ''auro, argento, aeri flando, feriundo''
# [[agris]] (‚Äúfields‚Äù)
#* '''''A.''' D. '''A.''' '' ‚Äî ''agris dandis adsignandis''
#* '''''A.''' I. '''A.''' '' ‚Äî ''agris judicandis adsignandis''
# {{lb|la|upon the voting tablets in judicial trials}} [[absolvo]] (‚ÄúI free‚Äù, ‚ÄúI acquit‚Äù)
# {{lb|la|in the Roman Comitia}} [[antiquo]] ‚Äî ‚ÄúI leave in its former state‚Äù, ‚ÄúI reject‚Äù [e.g. the point in question]
# [[amicus|amic≈ç]] (‚Äúfriend‚Äù)
#: '''''A.''' O.'' ‚Äî ''amico optimo'' ‚Äî ‚Äúbest friend‚Äù
# ''[[a]]'' (‚Äúof, from‚Äù)
#: '''''A.''' P.'' ‚Äî ''a populo''
# aediliciae
#: '''''A.''' P.'' ‚Äî ''aediliciae potestatis''
# [[aerario]]
#: '''''A.''' P. R.'' ‚Äî ''aerario populi Romani''
# {{lb|la|in Cicero's ''Tusculanae Disputationes'', ‚ÄúTusculan Disputations‚Äù}} ''[[adulescens]]'' or ''[[auditor]]'', one of the disputants, as opposed to ''M.'' for ''[[magister]]'' or ''[[Marcus]]''

