==Luxembourgish==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/a/|[aÀê]|lang=lb}}
** {{rhymes|aÀê|lang=lb}}

===Etymology 1===

====Letter====
{{head|lb|letter|lower case|a}}

# {{Latn-def|lb|letter|1|a}}

====See also====
* {{list:Latin script letters/lb}}

===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|lb|goh|ouga}}, from {{inh|lb|gem-pro|*aug√¥}}, ultimately from {{der|lb|ine-pro|*h‚ÇÉek ∑-||eye; to see}}. The phonetic development in Luxembourgish is regular: Old High German ''-ou-'' becomes ''-ƒÅ-''; intervocalic ''-g-'' is lost; word-final short vowels are apocopated.

====Noun====
{{lb-noun|n|Aen}}

# [[eye]]
#: ''Ech hunn eppes am '''A.'''''
#:: I have something in my '''eye.'''

===Etymology 3===
From {{inh|lb|gmh|ouwe}}, from {{inh|lb|goh|ouwa}}, from {{inh|lb|gem-pro|*awj≈ç}}. Cognate with {{cog|de|Aue}}, {{cog|en|eyot}}, {{cog|is|ey}}, {{cog|da|√∏}}, {{cog|sv|√∂}}.

====Noun====
{{lb-noun|f}}

# {{lb|lb|only used in place names}} [[floodplain]], [[meadow]]

[[Category:lb:Anatomy]]

