{{also|Crow}}
==English==
[[Image:Corvus brachyrhynchos 2.jpg|thumb|A bird; a crow: ''American crow'']]

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/k…π…ô ä/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|kr≈ç}}, {{IPA|/k…πo ä/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-crow.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|…ô ä|lang=en}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|crowe|sc=Latn}}, from {{inh|en|ang|crƒÅwe}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*krƒÅw≈ç}} (compare {{cog|fy|krie}}, {{cog|nl|kraai}}, {{cog|de|Kr√§he}}), from {{m|gem-pro|*krƒÅhanƒÖ}} ‚Äòto crow‚Äô. See below.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[bird]], usually black, of the genus ''[[Corvus]]'', having a strong conical beak, with projecting bristles; it has a harsh, croaking call.
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=1922|author=E.R. Eddison|title=The Worm Ouroborus|passage=Gaslark in his splendour on the golden stairs saying adieu to those three captains and their matchless armament foredoomed to dogs and '''crows''' on Salapanta Hills.}}
# A bar of iron with a beak, crook, or claw; a bar of iron used as a lever; a [[crowbar]].
#* {{quote-book|lang=en|year=1796|author=Matthew Lewis|title=The Monk|publisher=Folio Society|year_published=1985|page=267|passage=He approached the humble tomb in which Antonia reposed. He had provided himself with an iron '''crow''' and a pick-axe: but this precaution was unnecessary.}}
#: {{syn|en|crowbar}}
# The cry of the [[rooster]].
#: {{syn|en|cock-a-doodle-doo}}
# A [[gangplank]] ([[corvus#Latin|corvus]]) used by the Roman navy to board enemy ships.
# {{lb|en|among butchers}} The [[mesentery]] of an [[animal]].

