===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|en|enm|ravene}}, {{m|enm|ravine}}, from {{der|en|fro|raviner|t=rush, seize by force}}, itself from {{m|fro|ravine|t=rapine}}, from {{der|en|la|rapina|t=plundering, loot}}, itself from {{m|la|rapere|t=seize, plunder, abduct}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{l|en|ravin}}, {{l|en|ravine}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{enPR|rƒÉv π…ôn}}, {{IPA|/Àà…π√¶v…ôn/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|√¶v…ôn|lang=en}}

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# [[rapine|Rapine]]; [[rapacity]].
# [[prey|Prey]]; [[plunder]]; food obtained by [[violence]].

